<div style="Border:solid 1px #000000; padding:7px; margin-bottom: 10px;">
<div style="text-align: center;">
<h1 id="toc0"><span><span style="text-decoration: underline;">What's this?</span></span></h1>
</div>
<p>The cack hard cinematic universe is home to a bunch of dumb stupid stuff, mostly weird crack fiction. Cack fiction, if you will. This is a world where things always take a turn for the stupid, farcical, and idiotic. This isn't a canon, but simply a hub to host crackfiction too stupid for LolFoundation.</p>
<p>Hidden in this collapsible are the general 'rules' which we adhere to when writing within the cack hard cinematic universe. If for whatever reason you want to write crack.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<ul>
<li>No one is good at their job unless the plot demands it.</li>
<li>Researcher Zyn Kiryu is the only person who is good at her job regardless of the situation.</li>
<li>If anyone has to suffer, it's Mr. Fish.</li>
<li>049 and Spanko are best buds. No exceptions!</li>
<li>'Cack Hard' installments must be a movie of some sort. Continuity is for suckers!</li>
<li>Bottledick is canon.</li>
<li>The Foundation is less of a jail and more of a hotel.</li>
<li>Bottledick is not canon.</li>
<li>SCP-055 is a sphere.</li>
<li>Dr. Cimmerian sent 650 million emails and crashed scipnet servers for a week.</li>
<li>Site-19 has an on-site burger king.</li>
<li>WWS is engaged in a bloody war with the Shark Punching Center.</li>
<li>Dr. Hamm and SCP-049 are 049-J's fathers.</li>
<li>fuck you.</li>
<li>If you write in the cack hard cinematic universe, just set this page as your content's parent page.</li>
<li>Mixing canons and doing things that don't make any logical sense is not only allowed but encouraged.</li>
<li>have fun, damn it. <strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><em>this is not a canon</em></span></strong>, more like a loose continuity of crack fiction that is all about writing the stupidest crap you can think of.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
